# Web (reactive frontend)

- API calls go through the generated/hand-written client in `web/src/api/`, which
  is generated from or hand-kept in sync with `contracts/openapi.yaml`. Never hand-roll
  a fetch call to a backend endpoint outside that client.
- [FILL IN: your state management pattern — e.g. "server state via React Query,
  local UI state via useState/signals, no global store for server data."]
- [FILL IN: component structure convention — e.g. "one component per file, colocated
  test file, colocated styles."]
- New component with any logic (not pure presentational) → component test with
  Testing Library. New user-facing flow → Playwright e2e test.
- Loading/error/empty states are required for every data-fetching component, not
  an afterthought — write them in the same pass as the happy path.
- Run lint + unit tests before calling frontend work done.
